AGI - In France there is a possible breakthrough in the investigation of the mysterious death of the small Emile Soleil>, which between 2023 and 2024 has deeply shaken the country: Four adults were arrested, including the baby's grandparents. Four people ended up in handcuffs today for "voluntary murder" and "broadwashing", announced Aix-en-Provence's attorney in a press release consulted by Le Figaro.
&nbsp;
For the disappearance and death of Emile, 2 and a half years, in July 2023 in the Alps region of the High Provence, now the grandfather Philippe Vedovini> and his wife and "two of their adult children", or the uncles of the small victim, read in the prosecutor's note, according to which "these police arrests fall into a phase of verification and comparison of the elements and information collected during the last months".
&nbsp;
"This morning, March 25, 2025, Philippe Vedovini and his wife, Emile Soleil's grandparents, as well as two of their adult children, were arrested on charges of voluntary murder and corpse occultation by the investigators of the Marseille gendarmerie research section," said Prosecutor Jean-Luc Blanchon. According to information collected by Le Figaro, these police stops are held in the premises of the Marseille gendarmerie research section. The identity of the other two people in custody, the uncle or the aunt of the child, was not immediately made known, but the investigation suddenly concentrated on the family circle.
&nbsp;
In addition, several other children of the family will be heard in a voluntary audience. According to the newspaper Le Figaro, the analysis of the planter, seized in recent days by about fifteen pollutants, was not decisive for the decision to arrest the four members of the Emile family.
&nbsp;
"The investigators are also carrying out forensic operations in different locations of the country," added the attorney, who specified that "an additional communication will be made following the conclusion of the ongoing actions". Grandparents' attorney, Isabelle Colombani, confirmed the Afp that they were placed in police custody. "I don't have any comments, I just found out," the lawyer said.
&nbsp;
Emile, two and a half years, had disappeared on 8 July 2023, after arriving for summer holidays in the second home of maternal grandparents, in the hamlet of Haut-Vernet, in the Alps of the High Provence. Despite several days of research by citizens and "judicial issues", no trace of the child was found. For nine months the investigation has produced nothing concrete, until the discovery, at the end of March 2024, by a passer, skull and teeth of the child, about 1.7 km from the village, or 25 minutes walk for an adult.
&nbsp;
On 14 March last, the investigators of the cell "Emile" of the Marseille research section, who for almost two years have tirelessly investigated the death of the little one, carried out a "night" blitz in Haut-Vernet (Alpi dell'Alta Provenza), where a large florist was seized. The funeral of the little one took place on 8 February last, in the basilica of Saint-Maximin-la-Sainte-Baume (Var), in the presence of the whole family.
&nbsp;
"The time of silence must give way to that of truth. We can't live without answers, we still don't know what happened to Emile," said the baby's grandparents in Bfmtv. Several hundred people have witnessed the religious function celebrated according to the rite of St. Pius V, according to the desire of the parents of Emile, fervent traditionalist Catholics like his grandparents.&nbsp;

